Description: Silence -Werror=unused-but-set-variable on offset in CacheChange.hpp
 Fedora's GCC plus Fast DDS's own -Werror flags `offset` (advanced in the loop
 increment but never read) as a build error. Mark it [[maybe_unused]] so the
 vendored Fast DDS build passes under Fedora hardening flags.
Origin: vendor-specific
Forwarded: no, to be filed at https://github.com/eProsima/Fast-DDS
Last-Update: 2026-06-03
--- a/include/fastdds/rtps/common/CacheChange.hpp
+++ b/include/fastdds/rtps/common/CacheChange.hpp
@@ -267,7 +267,7 @@
             {
                 // Keep index of next fragment on the payload portion at the beginning of each fragment. Last
                 // fragment will have fragment_count_ as 'next fragment index'
-                size_t offset = 0;
+                [[maybe_unused]] size_t offset = 0;
                 for (uint32_t i = 1; i <= fragment_count_; i++, offset += fragment_size_)
                 {
                     set_next_missing_fragment(i - 1, i);  // index to next fragment in missing list
